{
  "texts": [
    "However, due to the innate opacity of machine learning models, lay users and even experts find it challenging to understand how a particular recommendation is generated (Peake & Wang, 2018; Zhang & Chen, 2020; Haque et al., 2023).",
    "Since it is impossible to understand the logic behind the outcome, users can only speculate on the reasons for a particular content suggestion.",
    "Explainable recommendations can help the target audience comprehend the reasons or logic behind a particular decision (Zhang & Chen, 2020).",
    "Explainable recommendations foster confidence, effectiveness, transparency, and satisfaction among users.",
    "In recent years, multiple explainable recommendation approaches have been proposed and implemented in real-world systems, particularly model-based methods in realworld systems."
  ]
}